/*
In html we can add css 3 way. In blew these three way given as example;
*/

1. Inline css:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>
<h1 style="color:blue;">A Blue Heading</h1>
<p style="color:red;">A red paragraph.</p>
</body>
</html>


<!-- ----------------------- -->
2. Internal css

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
 <style>
  body {background-color: powderblue;}
  h1 {
     color: blue;
     text-align:center;
     border:5px dotted #AFAE00;
  }
  p    {color: red;}
 </style>
</head>

<body>
<h1> Hello World </h1>
<p> Hello World </p>
<p>This is a paragraph.</p>

</body>
</html>


<!-- ----------------------- -->
3. External css:


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>

<h1>This is a heading</h1>
<p>This is a paragraph.</p>

</body>
</html>

css page:
____________________________________
body {
  background-color: powderblue;
}
h1 {
  color: blue;
}
p {
  color: red;
}
____________________________________

